A training aircraft owned by the International Aviation College (IAC) belly-landed yesterday at the Runway 23 of the Ilorin International Airport. The aircraft, a Diamond DA 42 with registration number 5N BNH made the landing at exactly 11:10am during a training exercise to get the student prepared for their final exams. Confirming the crash, Rector of the College, Engineer Benedict Adeyelika said the aircraft is currently under assessment by investigators from the Accident Investigation Bureau (AIB) and that the aircraft had sustained minor damages from the landing. He stated that it was important not to speculate the crash as the AIB were on top of the situation and the college was ensuring that it gives the investigators all the support, data they need to determine the cause. The AIB Spokesman, Mr. Tunji Oketumbi also confirmed the Bureau has commenced investigation into the occurrence.